description:
&lt;p&gt;A vacancy has arisen for a part time Medical Secretary in our busy Ear, Nose and Throat Department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be working with Consultants in a busy Secretarial office, providing secretarial support to all clinicians.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The emphasis is on the team working in a supportive administration team. Good communication and organisational skills are essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Some of the benefits of working at YDH include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working for a Trust voted 1st for Health and Well-being across the UK (NHS staff survey)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full NHS terms and conditions including extensive holidays, Agenda for Change pay with enhancements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Discounts for local and national retailers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dedicated well-being services for all employees&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible working where possible&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a part time position, 29.5 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jessica Whatley&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Operational Service Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jessica.whatley@ydh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
